  Scenario: Accessing a non-existing property with string should work
    Given an empty graph
    And having executed:
      """
      CREATE ()
      """
    When executing query:
      """
      WITH 'prop' AS prop
      MATCH (n) RETURN n[prop] AS result
      """
    Then the result should be, in any order:
      | result |
      | null   |
    And no side effects

